# NOVOALIGN BASIC MANUAL

###NOVOALIGN

Novoalign is use to align the fasta/fastq(sequence) file to the refence genome to get the number of sequence that is related with the reference genome.

### Basic command 

novoalign <option> <-d indexfile> <-f sequencefile> <-o outputfile>

### Option
-c <digit>
set the thread for number of cpu use. if not use the default will use maximun number of thread/cpu available
-t <digit>
set the threshold. threshold is use for use to define the alignment score that is acceptable be use score in mapped in output file.
-o 
set the format of the output file either native of sam.
-a
strip the -3 adapter region before the align
-r
for reporting the multimapped into the bam file. Can be selected to either <All> <None> <Random>

### Example

novoalign -c 5 -t 60 -d thaliana.idx -f seq.fq seq2.fq -o full.sam

*****


# NOVOINDEX

novoindex is to index the reference genome so it can be use as refence genome when align process is invoke.

### Basic command

novoindex <option> <name_of_indexfile.idx> <name_of_reference_genome>

### Option

-k <number> 
the k is to set the k-mer of the reference.k-mer is to set the length of sting  of the of the index file.(optional)
-s <number>
the s is to set the step size of index reference.(optional)

### Example

novoindex thaliana.idx arabidopsis_thaliana.TAIR10.fq
